I look at it like this:<P>It was Mythic's screw up.  If people can attack and kill the merchants, then we're in our right to be able to charm them.<P>If Mythic keeps those merchants hostile, yet makes us unable to charm them, that would be insensible.  Why not *add* more merchants there so there's an ample supply, some to (try) to sell to, and some to charm?<P>It *is* a rather nifty effect, and I suspect it'd be most useful in long Frontier defenses, for the arrow reason but maybe also ram equipment and what not.
